## React Standards

### Architecture
```
src/
├── components/       # Reusable UI components (dumb, no business logic)
├── pages/            # Route-level components
├── hooks/            # Custom hooks (all business logic lives here)
├── services/         # API calls only
├── store/            # State management (Zustand or Context)
├── types/            # TypeScript interfaces/types
├── utils/            # Pure utility functions
└── constants/        # App constants, config
```

### Component Rules
- Functional components ONLY — no class components
- TypeScript interfaces for all props (no `any`)
- Custom hooks for all data fetching and business logic
- Components max 150 lines — split if larger
- One component per file
- Named exports for components (not default export)

### State Management
- Local state: useState, useReducer
- Server state: React Query / TanStack Query (mandatory for API data)
- Global state: Zustand (lightweight) or React Context (simple cases)
- Never put API response directly in useState — use React Query

### Error Handling Pattern
```typescript
// Every page/feature component wraps with ErrorBoundary
// Every async operation handles loading + error + empty states
const { data, isLoading, error } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['users', filters],
  queryFn: () => userService.getUsers(filters),
  staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1000, // 5 min cache
});

if (isLoading) return <SkeletonTable rows={10} />;
if (error) return <ErrorState message="Unable to load users. Please try again." onRetry={refetch} />;
if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState message="No users found." action={<AddUserButton />} />;
```

### Performance Rules
- React.memo for expensive pure components
- useMemo for expensive calculations
- useCallback for functions passed as props
- Lazy loading: React.lazy() + Suspense for route-level code splitting
- Virtual scrolling: react-virtual for lists > 100 items
- Image optimization: WebP format, lazy load with loading="lazy"

### PWA Standards
- Service Worker: Workbox for caching strategy
- Cache strategy: Network-first for API, Cache-first for assets
- Offline page: custom offline.html shown when no connection
- Installable: manifest.json with icons, theme_color, display: standalone
- Push notifications: only if genuinely useful (not spam)

### Form Standards
- React Hook Form for all forms (not controlled inputs)
- Zod for schema validation
- Show validation errors inline, not on submit only
- Debounce API-dependent validation (email uniqueness check)
- Disable submit button while submitting (prevent double submit)
- Show success feedback immediately after submission

### API Service Pattern
```typescript
// services/userService.ts
const userService = {
  getUsers: async (filters: UserFilters): Promise<User[]> => {
    const response = await apiClient.get('/api/v1/users', { params: filters });
    return response.data.data;
  },
  createUser: async (data: CreateUserDTO, idempotencyKey: string): Promise<User> => {
    const response = await apiClient.post('/api/v1/users', data, {
      headers: { 'Idempotency-Key': idempotencyKey }
    });
    return response.data.data;
  }
};
```
